author: Inside Edition
description: Eric Kang and his son, Cashmere, are from Canada and now the duo have set up shop on a Brooklyn street to sell Christmas trees. "It does come with its challenges. We're out here in the cold and the rain … the wind," Eric says. They are living where they work, a curbside trailer. Eric was interviewed in a new documentary called "Merchants of Joy." The Amazon Prime Video film takes a look at five families who dominate the tree selling business in New York.
title: New Documentary Follows Five NYC Families In Tree Selling Business

author: Inside Edition
description: Timothee Chalamet and Kylie Jenner put break-up rumors to rest as they appeared together at the premiere of Chalamet's new movie "Marty Supreme." The couple looked striking in matching orange leather outfits. The movie is based on the life of Marty Reisman, a ping pong champion who became world champion at age 19. Inside Edition stopped into Ping Pod, a thriving chain of table tennis clubs for a lesson.
title: Timothee Chalamet And Kylie Jenner Stun At 'Marty Supreme' Premiere

author: Inside Edition
description: Nerves were frayed after a woman was given a glass full of liquor and a lighter to caramelize meringue. Luckily, no one was hurt. Flaming dessert accidents happened before. Three people were injured in another flaming dessert accident after a banana foster cart blew up. Inside Edition went to Gage and Tollner restaurant in Brooklyn to see how to make a flaming dessert, safely.
title: Tips On How Safely To Make A Flaming Dessert

author: Inside Edition
description: An alleged porch pirate is getting flagged by local police. The Fort Worth Police posted this home surveillance video to Facebook, showing an Amazon package being delivered to a home. Just moments later, it's snatched up by someone who doesn't take it in the house. He runs away with it in the other direction.
title: Alleged Porch Pirate Wearing Cowboys Jersey Sought By Cops #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A Virginia liquor store has turned a hilarious Black Friday mishap with a drunk raccoon into a business opportunity. A mischievous raccoon broke into the Virginia ABC store via the ceiling, after hours, and went on a bender. The store manager clocked in to work the next morning to discover 14 damaged bottles of spirits, and the bandit passed out on the bathroom floor. Now, they're making the most of the mishap. Inside Edition Digital has more.
title: Virginia Liquor Store Turns Drunk Raccoon Mishap Into Clever Cocktails

author: Inside Edition
description: Accused assassin Luigi Mangione looked into a camera and pumped his first as his pre-trial hearing continued Monday.
title: Who Are The Mangionistas? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A freight train crashed into a driver outside Cedar Rapids, Iowa. The driver survived the devastating impact. Inside Edition spoke exclusively to father-of-two Logan Gregoire, who suffered no major injuries. Gregoire says a building blocked his view of the approaching train and he didn't see the flashing light until it was too late. The accident happened as he was taking his car to the shop and his wife was in the car behind him and saw the whole thing. Gregoire says he's grateful to be alive.
title: Man Survives Train Crashing Into His Car

author: Inside Edition
description: Melissa McCarthy showed off her dramatic weight loss hosting "Saturday Night Live." The 55-year-old actress flaunted her slimming down in a black velvet jumpsuit, accentuated with a belt that cinched her waist. Viewers at home posted live comments about her appearance. It is estimated she lost between 75 and 100 pounds.
title: Melissa McCarthy Flaunts Dramatic Weight Loss on 'SNL'

author: Inside Edition
description: Meghan Markle says she reached out to her father during his medical crisis, but her father says she did not. Doctors say they had to amputate Thomas Markle's left leg below the knee after finding "a massive blood clot in his thigh." The 81-year-old to The Mail, "I don't want to die estranged from Meghan. I want to meet my grandkids." He has never seen Meghan and Prince Harry's two children. Meghan's spokesperson insisted she did reach out to her dad. Now, Meghan's half-brother is coming forward.
title: Tension Between Meghan Markle And Her Dad After Medical Emergency

author: Inside Edition
description: Accused assassin Luigi Mangione looked into a camera and pumped his first as his pre-trial hearing continued Monday. To Terrie Martin, a colleague of slain healthcare executive Brian Thompson, it's the latest outrage that has turned Mangione into a folk hero. Martin says she is appalled at the small army of young women who call themselves "Mangionistas" and show up every day at the hearing. Inside Edition caught up with two Mangione supporters outside the courthouse Monday.
title: Brian Thompson's Colleague Appalled By Luigi Mangione Supporters

author: Inside Edition
description: An American citizen was chased by ICE agents who thought she was in the country illegally. Jacelynn Guzman says she was born in the United States. ICE says Guzman matched a description of a woman they were looking for. US citizens being caught in sweeps as ICE against look for undocumented migrants has become a scene happening across America. The Department of Homeland Security has not released figures on how many citizens have been detained, but published reports say 170 have been held.
title: Masked ICE Agents Caught On Camera Chasing US Citizen

author: Inside Edition
description: President Donald Trump hosted the Kennedy Center Honors Sunday night and had some zingers. Trump's hosting gig was the cherry on top of his Kennedy Center takeover. All the honorees were personally approved by the president. Trump was accompanied by First Lady Melania, and he was asked about joking around that he might rename the Kennedy Center after himself. Among the guests were Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth and his wife Jennifer.
title: President Donald Trump Hosts Kennedy Center Honors

author: Inside Edition
description: A news anchor is fighting back against trolls and their insults about her weight. In her best news anchor voice, Carissa Codel read some of the meanest comments. Inside Edition's Ann Mercogliano spoke with the Ozarks First anchor in Missouri. "I get shocked by the people who seem genuinely angry who continue to comment about my weight," Codel says. "You can be happy with yourself. If you know who you are, nothing can hurt you."
title: News Anchor Reads Mean Comments About Her Weight
